				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\gamma (t)$$\end{document} (solid line) first progresses slower, then faster than the original clock time. Figure 1F illustrates how alignment by time-warping may better summarize the time-series in Fig. 1A and extract salient features and their variability. The time-series are now dilated or compressed according to the signal’s shape. Figure 1G shows the temporal transformations of all signals as a collection of warping functions \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
